# Both keys are optional — Furnace auto-generates them at startup if unset.
# Set them explicitly only if you need stable values across restarts.
#
# FURNACE_SESSION_HASH_KEY: keeps login sessions valid across restarts.
#   Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
#
# FURNACE_API_KEY: authenticates admin API calls (curl, CI scripts).
#   Copy from Admin UI → Config → Admin API Key after first start.

# FURNACE_SESSION_HASH_KEY=
# FURNACE_API_KEY=

# WebAuthn (passkey) relying-party config.
# Both default to localhost / http://localhost:<port> at startup, so no config
# is needed for local dev or Docker-on-same-machine.
# Set explicitly only when deploying to a custom domain.
#
# FURNACE_WEBAUTHN_RP_ID: domain only — no scheme, no port.  e.g. example.com
# FURNACE_WEBAUTHN_ORIGIN: full origin the browser connects to. e.g. https://example.com
#
# FURNACE_WEBAUTHN_RP_ID=
# FURNACE_WEBAUTHN_ORIGIN=
